title: An 'oddball' 6.0 earthquake is recorded almost 800 miles off Southern California's coast
dc:creator: Grace Toohey
description: The 6.0 magnitude earthquake in the north Pacific was recorded just before 10 p.m. Tuesday, intriguing scientists for its location far from fault lines.
content:encoded: The 6.0 magnitude earthquake in the north Pacific was recorded just before 10 p.m. Tuesday, intriguing scientists for its location far from fault lines.
